events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Elfrid Payton and Julius Randle scored 22 points apiece to power the New York Knicks to a 110-99 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Payton, Randle help power Knicks past Lillard, Blazers

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes had 28 points and seven rebounds to help offset a career-high 50 points by Denver’s Nikola Jokic, and the Sacramento Kings beat the Nuggets 119-114 on Saturday to complete a season sweep.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic scores 50 but Nuggets tripped up by Kings 119-114

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine bounced back from a poor performance a night earlier and scored 39 points Saturday as the Chicago Bulls routed the injury-plagued Orlando Magic 118-92.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine scores 39 points to lift Bulls past Magic, 118-92

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid scored 33 points and Ben Simmons had 16 points, 12 rebounds and eight assists to lead the Philadelphia 76ers to a 124-108 victory over the short-handed Brooklyn Nets on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid, Simmons lead 76ers past short-handed Nets 124-108

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 28 points and 13 assists, Clint Capela finished with 23 points and 16 rebounds, and the Atlanta Hawks held off the Toronto Raptors 132-121 to snap a three-game losing streak Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young, Capela pace Hawks in 132-121 win over Raptors

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 24 points and 11 rebounds, Jrue Holiday scored 20 and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Cleveland Cavaliers for the second time in two days, 124-99 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 24 as Bucks bury Cavaliers 124-99

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 30 points and the San Antonio Spurs held off a late charge from the Houston Rockets for a 111-106 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan has 30 as Spurs hold on for 111-106 win over Rockets

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Darius Bazley made the tiebreaking layup with 1:16 to play after Oklahoma City had blown a 23-point lead, and the Thunder beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 120-118 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder score 83 in half, then rally to edge Wolves 120-118

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic tied his career high with 42 points in a scoring duel with Stephen Curry, leading the Dallas Mavericks to a 134-132 victory over the Golden State Warriors on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic tops Curry in duel as Mavericks beat Warriors 134-132

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram had 27 points, 12 rebounds and a career-high four blocks, Zion Williamson capped a 29-point night with a game-sealing dunk in the final minute, and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Memphis Grizzlies 118-109 on Saturday night for...
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram, Williamson power Pelicans past Grizzlies, 118-109

events.name: Detroit Pistons at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored eight of his 33 points in the second overtime, Anthony Davis added 30 points and the Los Angeles Lakers narrowly avenged a loss in Detroit last month with a 135-129 victory over the undermanned Pistons on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron takes charge in 2nd OT, Lakers edge Pistons 135-129
